org.jemmy.dock

Class DockGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • org.jemmy.dock.DockGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.annotation.processing.Processor
    Deprecated. 
    Please use a generator from JemmySupport

    @Deprecated
@SupportedSourceVersion(value=RELEASE_6)
public class DockGenerator
extends javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
    Major inconvenience which a novice experiences with Jemmy usage is the fact that it is not clear from API what kind of operation you would be able to perform with what kind of controls. Similarly it is not at first clear what kind of lookup criteria one could use for a particular controls kind and also what properties a control type provides.
    This annotation processor generates another layer of API to access the same functionality which Jemmy provides but differently - through a set of lookup constructors, property getters and as* interfaces. All of that is generated from a set of annotations which are added to classes which extend org.jemmy.control.Wrap class.
    Check *.*Dock classes and the corresponding Wrap extentions within JemmyAWT code.
    Author:
    shura
